headline: SkyWest, Inc. Announces Second Quarter 2025 Profit
summary: ST. GEORGE, Utah, July 24, 2025--SkyWest, Inc. (NASDAQ: SKYW) ("SkyWest") today reported financial and operating results for Q2 2025, including net income of $120 million, or $2.91 per diluted share, compared to net income of $76 million, or $1.82 per diluted share, for Q2 2024.

headline: American Airlines shares fall on weak forecast
summary: American Airlines shares tumbled Thursday as the carrier projected a third-quarter loss due to lingering weakness in the US leisure market.The carrier projected a third-quarter loss of between 10 and 60 cents per share, and offered a full-year forecast range of between a loss of 20 cents and a gain of 80 cents per share.

headline: Southwest, American Stocks Fall After Earnings. Why the Airline Rally Is Faltering.
summary: Southwest Airlines  and  American Airlines  stocks were both falling early Thursday as investors were left disappointed by the carriers’ second-quarter earnings reports and commentary.  Although both noted improving travel demand, that wasn’t enough for investors.  The moves come after airline stocks have soared this earnings season.
